Job Description:
The *Director of Product *must have ability to:
Direct the end-to-end life cycle for employer’s software and financial technology products;
Define product strategy and work with engineering, user experience design, quality assurance and various other internal teams to build customer specific technical products;
Manage cross-functional teams including operations, sales, and finance towards achieving company’s business goals;
Determine customer needs and ensure correct specifications for technical products;
Understand market and competitive landscape to assess product opportunities and build business plans;
Design and track metrics at the product and company level to oversee overall direction and business strategy;
Manage and mentor product managers;
Work directly with CEO and CTO on long-term company vision.
Required: *
4+ years of product management experience building software products;
Experience in e-commerce, payments, or financial services;
Strong analytical skills;
Ability to leverage technology and programming tools to build and track detailed statistical, financial and business models;
Proficiency Microsoft Office suite and Visual Basic;
Strong project management and communication skills with ability to influence across different functional groups;
Master's degree in computer science or related engineering discipline; MBA or other advanced degree preferred.
